sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K371019
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: pdu(Propanediol utilization)BMC shell gene under Plac control
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite consists of eight pdu bacterial microcompartment(BMC) structure gene following a natural lac promotor(BBa_R0010). These genes come from four basic parts,pduAB,pduJK,pduN and pduTUV, which consist of the natural RBS and gene separately.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Zhang, Ruijun Zhu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Citrobactor freudii, the strain was bought from NITE Biological Resource Center (NBRC). NBRC NO. is 12681. History:IFO 12681 <- Ajinomoto Co., Inc. (AJ 2619) <- ATCC 8090 <- C.H. Werkm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Promotor BBa_R0010 was chosen to give a mediate transcription efficiency after induced by IPTG.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K371001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Pdu, a abbreviation of propanediol utilization, is name of operon which is used for degradation propanediol to generate energy. Pdu operon consist of 21 genes. Some of these genes encode a series proteins which assemble to a large icosahedral protein complex. PduAB consist of pdu A and pdu B wich their corresponding natural RBS, which got from Citrobacter Freundii by PCR. PduAB, together with others struture part of pdu operon such as pdu JK, can be used to construct a empty proteinous microcompartment in bacteria.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Zhang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pduJK come from Citrobacter Freundii genenom(NBRC NO.12681)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequencing result show that the gene of pduAB has some silent mutations, which have no effect on the function of protein.
